The paper deals with the complexity of depth-3 circuits, which are a fundamental object of study in computational complexity theory. The paper provides a new rank bound for depth-3 circuits, which is a central question in the field of circuit complexity. This makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from linear algebra and combinatorics, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the factorization pattern of depth-3 circuits, which suggests that cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
